          <div class="fundraiser-qa-item" id="qa-item-not-thinkup">
            <header>We’re just as proud of what ThinkUp <em>doesn’t do</em>:</header>
            <div class="content">
              <ul>
                <li>ThinkUp does NOT do things with your personal data behind your back.</li>
                <li>We do NOT try to turn your social network into a popularity contest about the number of followers you have.</li>
                <li>ThinkUp does NOT try to assign some point score to you based on how you talk to your friends.</li>
                <li>We are NOT trying to offer reporting on brand impressions for conversion funnels</li>
                <li>We’ll never lock your information into some proprietary system, since ThinkUp is completely open source.</li>
                <li>ThinkUp does NOT change its terms of service all the time without telling you about it.</li>
                <li>We do NOT tolerate people being jerks to each other in our developer community;  After almost four years, our mailing list has never had a flame war.</li>
                <li>We will NOT build self-driving cars or buy fancy racing yachts. (This is an easy promise to keep.)</li>

              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="fundraiser-qa-item" id="qa-item-goal">
            <header>What’s the goal of this campaign?</header>
            <div class="content">
              <p>We want to build another great Internet company, one that’s more focused on doing the right thing for its users and their communities than on taking over the whole web. We're starting by making an app that shows people exactly how meaningful their online interactions can be.</p>

              <p>Tens of thousands of geeky people have tried early beta versions of ThinkUp, but now we want to make it easy for anyone to use the app. So we are asking our community to subscribe to support the cost of developing ThinkUp into a reliable service backed by a sustainable company.</p>

              <p>You can pledge to subscribe to ThinkUp at the Member, Developer or Executive level, and be one of the very first users of ThinkUp in early 2014. When you do, you’ll help make ThinkUp available to everyone.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="fundraiser-qa-item" id="qa-item-what-i-get">
            <header>What do I get for backing ThinkUp?</header>
            <div class="content">
              <p>Every subscriber at every level gets great <strong>Member</strong> benefits as soon as we launch:</p>

              <ul>
                <li>Be first in line to reserve your name on ThinkUp, and have immediate access when we launch in early 2014.</li>
                <li>All of ThinkUp’s dozens of insights, with support for Facebook, Twitter, Instagram, Google+, YouTube and Foursquare.</li>
                <li>Invites for your friends to try out ThinkUp.</li>
                <li>An exclusive, brand new e-book, Insights, which explains what matters in social networking based on interviews with dozens of the most creative and influential users of social media.</li>
                <li>The ability to weigh in on changes to ThinkUp’s features, terms of service and product roadmap before those changes happen.</li>
              </ul>

              <p>The <strong>Pro</strong> level is great for experts and geeks, with support for more social networking accounts, access to new beta ThinkUp features as they’re developed, and APIs and data services for building cool apps on top of ThinkUp. You can also weigh in on which open source features from the community make their way into ThinkUp.</p>

              <p>At the <strong>Executive</strong> level, you get all of the benefits of the other levels, plus you get access to our company’s inner workings. You’ll get email updates direct from ThinkUp’s founders with information about exactly where we’re headed, and what changes or improvements we’re going to make. This level is great for businesses, developers or organizations that rely on ThinkUp or that want to be directly involved in making the web better. You’ll also get a personalized version of the Insights book, inscribed with a message from our founders that’s custom-tailored to how you use social networks.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

