              <ul class="faq">
                <li class="faq-item">
                  <div class="faq-question">Isn’t ThinkUp open source? Can I run it on my own? Is ThinkUp.com any different?</div>
                  <div class="faq-answer">Yes! ThinkUp is totally open source, and if you know how to run it on your own web server, we think that’s awesome and want you to do it. But the vast majority of folks we talk to have said they want a service they can just sign up for and use, so that’s what we’re building. We don’t have any features currently planned for ThinkUp.com that aren’t available in the version you would download from GitHub, except for ease of use.</div>
                </li>

                <li class="faq-item">
                  <div class="faq-question">I’m a developer! How can I build insights for ThinkUp?</div>
                  <div class="faq-answer">So glad you asked! We’ve documented ThinkUp’s insights API here, and even created a style guide for how insights should look and feel.</div>
                </li>

                <li class="faq-item">
                  <div class="faq-question">Is ThinkUp just a stats or analytics app? How does it compare to my existing analytics program?</div>
                  <div class="faq-answer">While we do have a few charts and graphs, the goal of ThinkUp is to tell you things that ordinary analytics apps don’t. So instead of focusing on how many followers you have, we want to offer more perspective on the content you’re sharing, and how it makes people feel and respond.</div>
                </li>
              </ul>
